In this article, President Trump responds to questions about various topics, including the ending of subsidies under Obamacare, the Iranian nuclear deal, healthcare negotiations, the opioid crisis, and the situation in Puerto Rico. Trump defends his decisions on healthcare and subsidies, stating that the money was going to insurance companies and not to the people. He also discusses the possibility of renegotiating the Iranian nuclear deal and expresses his dissatisfaction with Iran's behavior. On the opioid crisis, Trump says that a national emergency declaration is being studied. Regarding Puerto Rico, Trump emphasizes the need to rebuild the island's infrastructure, particularly the electric plants. He also addresses the North Korean situation, stating that the US is prepared for various scenarios and is open to negotiation if possible.